The paper deals with pseudodeterministic constructions, which are related to computational complexity and cryptography. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the construction of sets and the analysis of their density, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the hardness versus randomness paradigm, which is a topic in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
